content:
Here's the result of running `cat -n` on /workspace/SheepVibes/.github/workflows/run-tests.yml:
     1	name: Run Backend Tests
     2	
     3	on:
     4	  push:
     5	    branches: [ '**' ]
     6	  pull_request:
     7	    branches: [ main ]
     8	
     9	jobs:
    10	  test:
    11	    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    12	
    13	    services:
    14	      # Start a Redis service container for the job
    15	      redis:
    16	        image: redis:alpine
    17	        # Expose port 6379 on the service container to be mapped to the host
    18	        ports:
    19	          - 6379/tcp
    20	        # Health check for a passwordless Redis service.
    21	        options: >-
    22	          --health-cmd "redis-cli ping"
    23	          --health-interval 10s
    24	          --health-timeout 5s
    25	          --health-retries 5
    26	
    27	    steps:
    28	    - name: Checkout code
    29	      uses: actions/checkout@v5
    30	
    31	    - name: Set up Python 3.13
    32	      uses: actions/setup-python@v6
    33	      with:
    34	        python-version: '3.13'
    35	        cache: 'pip' # Cache pip dependencies
    36	
    37	    - name: Install dependencies
    38	      run: |
    39	        python -m pip install --upgrade pip
    40	        pip install -r backend/requirements.txt -r backend/requirements-dev.txt
    41	
    42	    - name: Run Pytest
    43	      env:
    44	        # Pass the dynamically assigned Redis host port to the tests.
    45	        CACHE_REDIS_PORT: ${{ job.services.redis.ports['6379'] }}
    46	      run: |
    47	        cd backend
    48	        python -m pytest -v
    49
